{"parse":{"title":"Philosophy Now Festival","pageid":57394022,"revid":857114083,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">Philosophy Now Festival</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nPhilosophy festival</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Frequency</th><td>\nEvery two years</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Location(s)</th><td>\nLondon</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited Kingdom</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Inaugurated</th><td>\n2011</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Sponsor</th><td>\nPhilosophy Now magazine</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Website</th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://philosophynow.org/festival\">https://philosophynow.org/festival</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Philosophy Now Festival</b> is a large philosophy festival held every two years in central London.\n</p><p>The Festival is hosted and organised by the newsstand magazine <a href=\"/wiki/Philosophy_Now\" title=\"Philosophy Now\">Philosophy Now</a>, which aims to take philosophy to the widest possible audience. The Festival is open to the general public, at little or no cost.\n</p><p>The first Philosophy Now Festival was held in 2011.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> It was held partly to mark the 20th anniversary of the launch of <a href=\"/wiki/Philosophy_Now\" title=\"Philosophy Now\">Philosophy Now</a> magazine.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Since then the Philosophy Now Festival has become a regular biannual event. The second <i>Philosophy Now</i> Festival was held in 2013,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> the third in 2015 and the fourth in January 2018.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Each festival was a one-day event involving contributions from more than a dozen philosophy organisations including <a href=\"/wiki/Philosophy_For_All\" title=\"Philosophy For All\">Philosophy For All</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Institute_of_Philosophy\" title=\"Royal Institute of Philosophy\">Royal Institute of Philosophy</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Venue\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Venue</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Against_Stupidity_Award\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Against Stupidity Award</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Venue\">Venue</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Philosophy_Now_Festival&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Venue\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Festival is held at <a href=\"/wiki/Conway_Hall\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Conway Hall\">Conway Hall</a>, a large art deco building in <a href=\"/wiki/Bloomsbury\" title=\"Bloomsbury\">Bloomsbury</a> in central London.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The Festival uses the entire building, and there are usually three or four events running at any one time.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Against_Stupidity_Award\">Against Stupidity Award</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Philosophy_Now_Festival&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Against Stupidity Award\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A regular feature of the Philosophy Now Festival is the presentation of the <i>Philosophy Now</i> Award for Contributions in the Fight Against Stupidity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-PNaward_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-PNaward-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> This always includes an acceptance speech, sometimes made via a video link.\n</p><p>Before the 2015 Philosophy Now Festival it was announced that the Award would for the first time be given to a children's author, <a href=\"/wiki/Cressida_Cowell\" title=\"Cressida Cowell\">Cressida Cowell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Philosophy_Now_Festival&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://now-here-this.timeout.com/2011/12/17/philosophy-now-festival/\">\"I Think, Therefore I Am Attending the Philosophy Now Festival\"</a>. <i>Time Out</i>. London. 17 December 2011.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Time+Out&amp;rft.atitle=I+Think%2C+Therefore+I+Am+Attending+the+Philosophy+Now+Festival&amp;rft.date=2011-12-17&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnow-here-this.timeout.com%2F2011%2F12%2F17%2Fphilosophy-now-festival%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APhilosophy+Now+Festival\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://philosophynow.org/issues/89/The_Philosophy_Now_Festival\">\"The Philosophy Now Festival\"</a>. <i>Philosophy Now</i>. London. March 2012.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Philosophy+Now&amp;rft.atitle=The+Philosophy+Now+Festival&amp;rft.date=2012-03&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fphilosophynow.org%2Fissues%2F89%2FThe_Philosophy_Now_Festival&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APhilosophy+Now+Festival\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://philosophynow.org/festival/2013\">\"Philosophy Now Festival 2013 | Philosophy Now\"</a>. <i>philosophynow.org</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 July</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=inf